subSection.paragraph:
Tor dongnaiensis
is recorded from the mainstream Đồng Nai River, where it is harvested by local fishers. As a result of the development of hydropower dams, including Đồng Nai 3 (
11 ° 52 ’ 20 ” N
107 ° 53 ’ 23 ” E
), Đồng Nai 4 (
11 ° 53 ’ 11 ” N
107 ° 43 ’ 37 ” E
), and Đồng Nai 5 (
11 ° 47 ’ 51 ” N
107 ° 32 ’ 57 ” E
), and sand exploitation activities, this species is facing a high threat. Given the available information, we suggest the species should be considered Near Threatened following IUCN’s Red List categories (
IUCN 2014 , version 11
).
